7.40	Ronan_Seamus_Farrow	Ronan Farrow	Ronan Farrow (born December 19, 1987) is an American human rights activist, freelance journalist, Rhodes Scholar, lawyer and government official. He is currently serving in the Obama administration as Special Adviser to the Secretary of State for Global Youth Issues and director of the State Department's Global Youth Issues office. He assumed his current role following two years as the State Department’s Special Adviser for Humanitarian and NGO Affairs in the Office of the Special Representative for Afghanistan and Pakistan. His writings have appeared in the Los Angeles Times, the International Herald Tribune, the Wall Street Journal and other publications, focused primarily on human rights issues in the Horn of Africa. He has appeared as a frequent commentator on major networks and as an expert witness before the U.S. Congressional Human Rights Caucus. A graduate of Yale Law School, much of his work has focused on engagement with marginalized actors such as youth and women’s groups.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1a/Ronan_Farrow_Headshot.jpg/220px-Ronan_Farrow_Headshot.jpg
